sub_title:
Operations Officer - Fox Global Express; Hobby Photographer 
Juris Doctorate (2014); Rotary Peace Fellow, Class XIV (2015-2017)
summary:
I am a US citizen living in the Netherlands since 2017. I am searching for work that will bolster my research and advocacy credentials while also building my documentary photography portfolio.

I have an educational background in US law, public opinion and voting behavior, and social science research. Through this, I have significant experience conducting desk and field research, both qualitative and quantitative. My work has explored the causes of conflict, and the human exploitation that results from conflict. I have focused this research on the conflicts in Sudan/Darfur and Syria.

I tie my research background to my passion for documenting personal, political, and cultural experiences through photography. I love gaining a deeper understanding of why people become involved in social movements, protests and demonstrations. This has given me the opportunity to explore Dutch music and cultural experiences, the LGBTQI community, and, recently, the Black Lives Matter protests in the Netherlands. 

I am driven to a career in documentary photography. I recognize this is something to be earned and not given. Over the past five years, I have established a foundation, which has allowed my work to be exhibited and shared across various platforms. I am motivated to continue working to make my goal a reality.
